Alright — here’s a **clear, step-by-step guide (CMD-based)** to run **TCP and UDP file transfer** AND how to **explain both in viva/demo**.

---

# 🧭 🟢 BEFORE YOU START

### 📁 Put all files in one folder:

```
tcp_server.cpp
tcp_client.cpp
udp_server.cpp
udp_client.cpp
send_file   (any file: txt/mp3/mp4)
```

---

# 💻 🟦 HOW TO RUN TCP (STEP-BY-STEP)

## 🔹 Step 1: Open CMD (Terminal 1)

Go to your folder:

```bash
cd Desktop\your_folder_name
```

---

## 🔹 Step 2: Compile TCP files

```bash
g++ tcp_server.cpp -o tcp_server
g++ tcp_client.cpp -o tcp_client
```

---

## 🔹 Step 3: Run Server FIRST

```bash
tcp_server
```

👉 Output:

```text
TCP Server waiting...
```

---

## 🔹 Step 4: Open NEW CMD (Terminal 2)

```bash
cd Desktop\your_folder_name
```

---

## 🔹 Step 5: Run Client

```bash
tcp_client
```

👉 Output:

```text
File sent successfully!
```

---

## 🔹 Step 6: Check Server Window

👉 You will see:

```text
File received successfully!
```

👉 File saved as:

```text
received_tcp_file
```

---

# 💻 🟪 HOW TO RUN UDP (STEP-BY-STEP)

## 🔹 Step 1: Compile

```bash
g++ udp_server.cpp -o udp_server
g++ udp_client.cpp -o udp_client
```

---

## 🔹 Step 2: Run UDP Server

```bash
udp_server
```

---

## 🔹 Step 3: Open NEW CMD

Run:

```bash
udp_client
```

---

## 🔹 Step 4: Output

Server:

```text
UDP File received!
```

Client:

```text
UDP File sent!
```

