# 🧠 ⚖️ EXPLAIN DIFFERENCE (VERY IMPORTANT)

| Feature     | TCP                 | UDP            |
| ----------- | ------------------- | -------------- |
| Type        | Connection-oriented | Connectionless |
| Reliability | High                | Low            |
| Speed       | Slower              | Faster         |
| Used for    | File transfer       | Streaming      |

---

# 🎤 🔑 VIVA EXPLANATION (SAY THIS)

### TCP:

> “TCP establishes a connection using a handshake, ensures reliable and ordered data delivery, and is used for file transfer.”

---

### UDP:

> “UDP sends data without establishing a connection, making it faster but unreliable, suitable for real-time applications.”

---

# ⚠️ COMMON ERRORS (IMPORTANT)

| Error               | Fix                      |
| ------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Port already in use | Restart CMD              |
| File not found      | Check `send_file` exists |
| No connection       | Run server first         |

